scopecontent.p:
Includes a letter from Edward Gordon Craig to his mother, Ellen Terry, about Isadora;
              his personal diary written between 1943-1947; correspondence and notes compiled by
              Allan Ross Macdougall for his biography, "Isadora, a Revolutionary in Art and Love";
              and a memoir of a 1921 performance by Isadora Duncan at Queen's Hall by journalist
              Henrietta Leslie.
